text:
To create a more vibrant website for the given mock screen, you can write simple HTML and JavaScript. Replace the two jokes with genuine jokes. Here's an example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Joke Website</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
  <p id="joke1">Why did the tomato turn red?</p>
  <p id="joke2">Because it saw the salad dressing!</p>
  <button onclick="changeJoke()">Change Joke</button>
  <script>
    function changeJoke() {
      var joke1 = document.getElementById("joke1");
      var joke2 = document.getElementById("joke2");
      var newJoke1 = "Why did the scarecrow win an award?";
      var newJoke2 = "Because he was outstanding in his field!";
      joke1.innerHTML = newJoke1;
      joke2.innerHTML = newJoke2;
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```
JavaScript:
```javascript
function changeJoke() {
  var joke1 = document.getElementById("joke1");
  var joke2 = document.getElementById("joke2");
  var newJoke1 = "Why did the tomato turn red?";
  var newJoke2 = "Because it saw the salad dressing!";
  joke1.innerHTML = newJoke1;
  joke2.innerHTML = newJoke2;
}
```
This code will display two genuine jokes on the website and provide a button to change them. When the button is clicked, the jokes will be replaced with new ones.
